strings : nameDiamond

Write a method named nameDiamond that accepts a string as a parameter and prints it in a "diamond" format as shown below.
For example, the call of nameDiamond("MARTY"); should print:

M
MA
MAR
MART
MARTY
 ARTY
  RTY
   TY
    Y

 public static void nameDiamond(String str) {
        for(int i = 0; i < str.length(); i++) {
            System.out.println(str.substring(0, i + 1));
        }
        for(int i = 1; i < str.length(); i++) {
            for(int n = 0; n < i; n++) {
                System.out.print(" ");
            }
            System.out.println(str.substring(i));
        }
    }
